Question: How to create a custom list view in Android?
Answer:
```java
public class CustomAdapter extends ArrayAdapter<String> {
    public CustomAdapter(Context context, String[] items) {
        super(context, R.layout.custom_row, items);
    }

    @Override
    public View getView(int position, View convertView, ViewGroup parent) {
        LayoutInflater inflater = LayoutInflater.from(getContext());
        View customView = inflater.inflate(R.layout.custom_row, parent, false);

        String item = getItem(position);
        TextView textView = (TextView) customView.findViewById(R.id.textView);
        textView.setText(item);

        return customView;
    }
}
```

In the second question, you are getting a NullPointerException because you are trying to use `findViewById()` before the view has been inflated. You should move the `findViewById()` call inside the `getView()` method, after the `inflate()` call.

In the third question, you are creating a custom adapter for a list view. The `ArrayAdapter` class is a base class for arrays of items. You can create a custom adapter by extending `ArrayAdapter` and overriding the `getView()` method. In the `getView()` method, you can inflate a custom layout for each item in the list and set the data for each item.

Please replace `R.layout.custom_row` and `R.id.textView` with your actual layout and text view ids.

